On December 4, 2020, the President signed several laws. These include the Rodchenkov Anti-Doping Act of 2019, which imposes criminal sanctions on individuals involved in doping fraud conspiracies and requires restitution for victims. The Internet of Things Cybersecurity Improvement Act of 2020 establishes security standards for IoT devices owned or controlled by the Federal government. The Greg LeMond Congressional Gold Medal Act of 2019 awards a Congressional Gold Medal to Greg LeMond for his contributions as an athlete, activist, role model, and community leader. The Negro Leagues Baseball Centennial Commemorative Coin Act requires the Department of the Treasury to mint and issue coins in commemoration of the 100th anniversary of the establishment of the Negro Leagues baseball. The President is also authorized to posthumously award the Medal of Honor to Alwyn C. Cashe for acts of valor during Operation Iraqi Freedom. The Impact Aid Coronavirus Relief Act modifies application requirements for the Impact Aid Program and requirements for allocations to states under the Migrant Education program. The Improving Safety and Security for Veterans Act of 2019 requires the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) to report to Congress on patient safety and quality of care, particularly at the VA medical center in Clarksburg, West Virginia. Lastly, the Department of Veterans Affairs Website Accessibility Act of 2019 requires the VA to study and report on the accessibility of its websites to individuals with disabilities.